cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Cross‑Implementation QUIC File Transfer Performance Dataset with Energy and
  Throughput Measurements
abstract: This dataset captures the results of coordinated client‑server file transfer
  experiments using multiple QUIC protocol implementations across two test nodes.
  For each run, a TLS‑enabled QUIC server delivered a payload of varying size under
  configurable bandwidth limits while recording energy consumption; the corresponding
  client measured start/end timestamps, verified checksums, and logged execution details.
  Aggregated logs were processed to compute elapsed time, goodput, success rates,
  and statistical summaries across implementation, bandwidth, file size, and repetition
  dimensions, with visualizations and JSON/TSV result files provided.
